thread.title: Aegon reports Q4 earnings above analysts' expectations

title: Aegon reports Q4 earnings above analysts' expectations
text: February 15, 2018 / 6:43 AM / Updated 38 minutes ago Aegon reports Q4 earnings above analysts' expectations Reuters Staff 1 Min Read AMSTERDAM, Feb 15 (Reuters) - Dutch insurer Aegon NV on Thursday reported better-than-expected earnings of 525 million euros ($654 million) for the fourth quarter, helped by cost cutting and higher fee revenues. Analysts polled for Reuters had seen underlying earnings at 512 million euros, compared with 554 million euros in the fourth quarter of 2016. $1 = 0.8024 euros Reporting by Toby Sterling; Editing by Subhranshu Sahu
